-- Spanish Train Derailment Kills at Least 35, El Pais Says
-- B y   J i m   S i l v e r
-- 2013-07-24T21:47:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-24/spanish-train-derailment-kills-at-least-35-el-pais-says.html
A train derailment in Spainâ€™s
northwestern Galicia region killed at least 35 people, newspaper
El Pais  reported , citing Alberto Nunez Feijoo, president of the
regional government.  A train traveling between  Madrid  and the Galician city of
Ferrol derailed when entering the station in Santiago de
Compostela at 8:41 p.m. local time, train operator Renfe said in
an e-mailed statement.  The train was traveling on the high-speed track and was
carrying 218 passengers, Renfe said, without providing any
figures for those killed or injured.  More than 50 people were injured in the crash, newspaper El
Mundo  said . A person living near the crash site said he heard an
explosion and saw a train car come off the rails, El Mundo said,
citing a report from Radio Galega.  To contact the reporter on this story:
